From the perspective that a movie spoiler will spoil the movie, I try to avoid them. At least when they are packaged specifically  as a spoiler. I think these can sometimes exist for malicious intent and I am not really interested in that sort of thing. But there are many instances when  I am seeking out a movie to watch and I will need to read plot summaries to determine how well it fits my interests. And in doing so, I will learn an important plot point that essential to the plot and could be considered a spoiler in some ways. These seem inadvertent and I am not bothered so much by the discovery. In these instances, I am usually very pleased to find a new movie and the spoiled plot is of little concern.

The reasons that I sometimes avoid trailers is because I feel that they sometimes offer an inauthentic summary of the film. But when I do stumble upon one by happenstance, I usually watch it just on the off chance something piques my interest.
